column1: If a product is in stock only once and the payment of the customer ordering this product fails or is aborted, it won't be available until the order is canceled (see timeout option below). Be careful though: If you enable this option, there is a chance that payments are made with the corresponding order being already canceled.
column2: If a product is in stock only once and the payment of the customer ordering this product fails or is aborted, it won't be available until the order is canceled (see timeout option below). Be careful though: If you enable this option, there is a chance that payments are made with the corresponding order being already canceled.
